    "active_lock_reason": null,
    "body": "## Problem\r\n\r\nWhen draft report is created in NewDot, the person who is supposed to take next action, ie submit the report should have GBR shown on that report in LHN.\r\n\r\nHowever, only in case of policy submission settings such that there is no scheduled submit set up.\r\n\r\n## Why is this important?\r\n\r\nWe should not be calling out the submitter to take action in case the report will get autosubmitted\r\n\r\n## Solution\r\n\r\nHandle the logic [here](https://github.com/Expensify/Auth/blob/085f5b81dd971b2e0fd664f75b9ef8d995a20015/auth/lib/Transaction.cpp#L1769) in auth to only add the GBR to the submitter if no autosubmission is set up on the policy.\r\n\r\nSame goes for optimistic data in the App.\r\n",
